survey.automatic_detection_helpful_explanation: It seemed to give many false positives when the sequence changed (e.g. from green-purple to green-orange. Because of this, I do not think I really trusted the detection.
survey.history_helpful_explanation: I found it harder to see if there 'odd ones out' were anomalies or part of a longer sequence rhythm, because there were less of the blocks on the width of the screen (of course, they were in the compressed view, but hard to incorporate in checking if part of the sequence because of their different size). I was unsure how the aggregated view could help me, since a sequence in a row could change during the three minutes. Because of this, the aggregated view seemed meaningless to me.
